					<description><![CDATA[“Children are an heritage of the Lord” — Psalm 127:3 Happy Aunt and Uncles Day. So, if my sister has a son, that makes me an uncle. If, instead, she has a daughter, does that make me an aunt? Just kidding. If you happen to&#160;<a class="read-more" href="https://llgt.cafe/aunt-and-uncles-day">&#8230;</a>]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p>“<strong>Children are an heritage of the Lord” — Psalm 127:3</strong></p>



<p>Happy Aunt and Uncles Day. So, if my sister has a son, that makes me an uncle. If, instead, she has a daughter, does that make me an aunt? Just kidding.</p>



<p>If you happen to make it to Spokane, Washington, there is an amazing bookstore called Aunties. You should go if you have a chance.</p>



<p>If you have a niece for nephew, don’t bother trying to get them to mow the lawn with you. It may work but probably won’t. Instead, take them out to eat or to a movie of their choosing. You may want to read to him or her. Just have fun together.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
